        "id": 4122767,
        "name": "alan weinberg",
        "username": "alan_weinberg",
        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/www.wineberserkers.com/alan_weinberg/{size}/647_2.png",
        "created_at": "2023-07-29T02:36:33.099Z",
        "cooked": "<p>young but wanted to try since the wife ordered white burgundy and Boillot is occasionally premoxed. Not this bottle. Started out quiet, took a little time to unfurl and then:  wow. Really great soft layered texture, like drinking mercury. Very intense and concentrated citrus and minerals, steely like CC should be, acid that tightens up the whole package and drives it like a laser into and through the palate.  Then it just fans out and hits every nook and cranny.  Fireworks!  Super wine.</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 6,
        "updated_at": "2023-07-29T02:36:33.099Z",
